        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:38PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Conrad, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shelby and Dunkirk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
